
                                            A Cape Town tour guide and a Japanese couple fell while climbing along the side of the mountain on Monday.
                                         CAPE TOWN - The circumstances surrounding the death of two climbers on Table Mountain is being investigated by a team of local experts. Investigators are focusing on the ropes and their position in relation to the mountain. A Cape Town tour guide and a Japanese couple fell while climbing along the side of the mountain on Monday. The woman survived the fall. Wilderness Search and Rescue's Johan Marais: "They were, as far as we know, on a regular route up the mountain when they somehow lost their footing and fell and ended up dangling from rope which they had secured to the mountain."